		<label>Fancy Gibbon</label>
		<description>A beautiful, genetically modified gibbon that has had its intelligence boosted to the point that it can understand the concept of money. This rare form of gibbon is used by orbital traders to win the hearts and minds of primitive, neolithic societies on the Rim in order to increase the amount of potential revenue by expanding the consumer base. A Fancy Gibbon understands the concept of money- something demonstrated teachable to most monkeys -but is capable of actually using it as a medium of exchange. This remarkable ability captivates sentient beings: just being near it tends to make people more... capitalistic. \n \n A gibbon, also known as the "lesser ape", is a type of tailless monkey (apes are monkeys) capable of swinging through trees and is the fastest tree-dwelling, flightless mammal on Old Earth. Unlike the greater apes (e.g. chimpanzees and gorillas), lesser apes are significantly smaller, do not form nests, cannot use tools unless genetically engineered to do so (as the Fancy Gibbon is), and often mate for life.</description>
